":"Bailly","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Armand, Emile, Marcel, Philippe.","French: occupational name for a steward or official, from Old French <i>baillif</i>. Compare   Bailey   4.","French: habitational name from (Le) Bailly, the name of several places in the northern part of France."]},{"name":"Bale","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone who lived by the outer wall of a castle, Middle English <i>bailli</i>, <i>baile</i>, from Old French <i>bail(le)</i> ‘enclosure’ (see   Bailey   3).","Breton (<b>Balé</b>): variant of   Balay  .","French: unexplained."]},{"name":"Baily","meanings":["English: variant of   Bailey  ."]},{"name":"Bayly","meanings":["English: variant of   Bailey  ."]},{"name":"Bayley","meanings":["English: variant of   Bailey  ."]},{"name":"Balay","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Rajesh, Satish.","Altered form of English   Bailey  .","French: habitational name from any of various minor places so named."]},{"name":"Baile","meanings":["Spanish: status name for a steward or official, from Old Spanish <i>baile</i>, Late Latin <i>baiulivus</i>; cognate with English   Bailey  .","French (southern): variant of   Bail  .","English: variant of   Bale  ."]},{"name":"Baillie","meanings":["Scottish:","from Older Scots <i>baillie</i>, <i>baili</i>. In Scotland, a baillie was a status name for any of various officials, including the chief magistrate in a barony and (later) the chief magistrate or administrative officer of a barony or district. Etymologically, this is the same word as English   Bailey  , but the functions as well as the spelling of the two officials were different in England and Scotland.","topographic name from Older Scots <i>bailli</i> ‘outer court of a castle’; see   Bailey   3 and   Bale   1."]},{"name":"Baley","meanings":["English: variant of   Bailey  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1647031,"age":0,"year":"1787","julianDay":2373749,"title":"The Making of the U.S. Constitution.","description":"The Philadelphia Convention was intended to be the first meeting to establish the first system of government under the Articles of Confederation. From this Convention, the Constitution of the United States was made and then put into place making it one of the major events in all American History.","url":"https://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/constitutional-convention-convenes-in-philadelphia","urlTitle":"The Philadelphia Convention","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1701452,"age":1,"year":"1788","julianDay":2374114,"title":"South Carolina becomes the 8th state in the Union","description":"On May 23, 1788, South Carolina ratifies the Constitution of the United States making it the 8th State of the Union.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/us-states/south-carolina","urlTitle":"History.com - South Carolina","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1352457,"age":21,"year":"1808","julianDay":2381418,"description":"Atlantic slave trade abolished.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1701455,"age":35,"year":"1822","julianDay":2386532,"title":"Slave Rebellion","description":"\"On June 16, 1822,  Denmark Vesey a free and self-educated African American leads a slave rebellion called \"\"the rising.\"\" The interesting thing about this rebellion is that it does not really happen. The only thing the judges have to go on is the testimony of people that witness it.\"","url":"http://time.com/4701283/denmark-vesey-history-charleston-south-carolina/","urlTitle":"Time.com - South Carolina","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1701456,"age":42,"year":"1829","julianDay":2389089,"title":"Fort Sumter Constructed","description":"In 1829 Fort Sumter is constructed in the Charleston Harbor, South Carolina. Fort Sumter is most known for being the site of the first shots of the Civil War. It is barely ready when the American Civil War starts.","url":"https://www.history.